    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-05-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-05-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="702"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d702">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/1732.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Ciudad
                            Juarez</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juarez</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-05-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 11, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Provisional President Madero and Provisional Governor Gonzales are here, and have
                    set up local government for Juarez. I am acting in harmony with the Government
                    de facto. The provisional governor seems anxious to favor Americans and work in
                    harmony with them in the establishment of law and order.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
